'''乌鲁木齐七五事件'''（{{Lang-ug|ئۈرۈمچی بەشىنچی ئىيۇل ۋەقەسى}}），中國大陸媒体和中華人民共和國政府称'''乌鲁木齐“7·5”打砸抢烧杀严重暴力犯罪事件'''<ref>{{cite web |title=新疆乌鲁木齐“七·五”打砸抢烧严重暴力犯罪事件 |url=http://www.chinanews.com/special/2009/07-07/xj.shtml |website=中国新闻网 |accessdate=2019-07-11 |date=2009-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702202936/http://www.chinanews.com/special/2009/07-07/xj.shtml |archive-date=2019-07-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是2009年7月5日在[[中华人民共和国|中华人民共和国]][[新疆维吾尔自治区|新疆维吾尔自治区]]首府[[乌鲁木齐市|乌鲁木齐市]]爆发的持续数日的大規模騷亂與暴力活動。起初只是一场示威活动，后演变成维吾尔族人针对[[汉族|汉族]]等非穆斯林族裔的無差別暴力袭击。至少1000餘名[[维吾尔族|维吾尔人]]参与了事件首日的暴動<ref name=bbc>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8135203.stm|title=Scores killed in China protests|publisher=BBC News|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2009-07-06|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66eRn433U?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8135203.stm|archive-date=2012-04-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>。中華人民共和国政府出动了[[中国人民武装警察部队|武装警察]]加以应对。两天后数百名受害者親屬意圖发起反击，与警方以及维吾尔人发生冲突。中華人民共和国政府称，这起事件造成至少197人死亡<ref name=CD197>{{cite news | url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/18/content_8444365.htm | title=Urumqi riot handled 'decisively, properly' | author=Hu Yinan, Lei Xiaoxun | date=2009-07-18 | accessdate=2009-07-18 | work=China Daily | archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p3p65NtT?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/18/content_8444365.htm | archivedate=2010-04-17 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=NYTtrials>{{cite news | work=The New York Times | date=2009-08-25 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/26/world/asia/26china.html | title=Chinese President Visits Volatile Xinjiang | last=Wong | first=Edward | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017095718/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/26/world/asia/26china.html | archive-date=2017-10-17 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，大部分為漢族人<ref name="Xinhua197">Yan Hao、Geng Ruibin、Yuan Ye，〈[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/18/content_11727782.htm Xinjiang riot hits regional anti-terror nerve] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5p3pHXm0l?url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/18/content_11727782.htm |date=20100417160415 |dateformat=iso }}〉，[[新华社|新华网]]，2009年7月18日，最后访问于2009年7月21日（原始内容于2010年4月17日）。</ref>，另有1721人受伤<ref name="scmp20090717">〈Initial probe completed and arrest warrants to be issued soon, Xinjiang prosecutor says〉，（原载《[[南華早報|南華早報]]》），[[美联社|美联社]]，2009年7月17日，A7页。</ref>，以及大量车辆、建筑物被摧毁。[[人权观察|人权观察]]报告43起于骚乱后数日的警方大规模清理行动中失踪之事件<ref name="upitt">{{cite news|last=Riley|first=Ann|date=2009-10-21|url=http://jurist.org/paperchase/2009/10/china-officials-disappeared-uighurs.php|title=China officials 'disappeared' Uighurs after Xinjiang riots: HRW|work=Paper Chase Newsburst|publisher=University of Pittsburgh School of Law|accessdate=2014-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019013812/http://jurist.org/paperchase/2009/10/china-officials-disappeared-uighurs.php|archive-date=2014-10-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并认为真实失踪人数会高得多<ref name="BBC8317644">{{cite news|last=Bristow|first=Michael|date=2009-10-21|accessdate=2010-02-25|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/8317644.stm|title=Many 'missing' after China riots|publisher=BBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121126054812/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/8317644.stm|archive-date=2012-11-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

6月尾广东韶关[[旭日玩具厂群体斗殴事件|旭日玩具厂群体斗殴事件]]造成两名维吾尔人死亡，7月5日有民衆發起要求对鬥毆进行全面调查的遊行，游行队伍与警方发生冲突之後爆發七五事件。<ref name="nyt0907052">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/06/world/asia/06china.html?ref=global-home|title=Riots in Western China Amid Ethnic Tension|work=The New York Times|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-07-05|last=Wong|first=Edward|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228024742/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/06/world/asia/06china.html?ref=global-home|archive-date=2013-12-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。但观察家对于抗议活动如何引发暴力活动之原因意见不一。[[中華人民共和國政府|政府]]称骚乱是[[热比娅·卡德尔|热比娅·卡德尔]]领导[[世界維吾爾代表大會|世界維吾爾代表大會]]在国外策划的<ref name="reut090705">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/06/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE56500R20090706|title=China calls Xinjiang riot a plot against its rule|agency=Reuters|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910175157/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/06/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE56500R20090706|archive-date=2012-09-10|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="timesonline2">{{cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article6644574.ece|title=China in deadly crackdown after Uighurs go on rampage|work=The Times|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-07-05|last=Macartney|first=Jane|location=London|archive-date=2020-05-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200515211718/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=timesonline>{{cite news | url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article6644574.ece | title=China in deadly crackdown after Uighurs go on rampage | work=The Times | date=2009-07-05 | accessdate=2009-07-05 | last=Macartney | first=Jane | location=London | archive-date=2020-05-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200515211718/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>，而热比娅否认她在[[东突厥斯坦独立运动#民族有自决权|维吾尔族自决]]的斗争中煽动暴力<ref name="profile0503172">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4357607.stm|work=BBC News|title=Profile: Rebiya Kadeer|date=2005-03-17|accessdate=2010-01-04|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66fiuUvbF?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4357607.stm|archive-date=2012-04-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。维吾尔流亡团体称，事态升级是由于警方过度使用武力<ref name="Timewestwar" /><ref name="afp090706">{{cite news|url=http://news.smh.com.au/breaking-news-world/three-die-during-riots-in-chinas-xinjiang-region-state-media-20090706-d9dz.html|agency=Agence France-Presse|publisher=Sydney Morning Herald|title=Three die during riots in China's Xinjiang region: state media|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-09-05|first=Marianne|last=Barriaux|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708112355/http://news.smh.com.au/breaking-news-world/three-die-during-riots-in-chinas-xinjiang-region-state-media-20090706-d9dz.html|archive-date=2009-07-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

中国媒体此次事件比較重視，常將其与[[2008年西藏骚乱|2008年西藏骚乱]]相比较<ref name="ft00144" />。骚乱开始後，新疆与外界的电话和互联网连接被切断。在随后的几个星期里，官方消息来源报告说，1000多名暴徒被拘留或逮捕<ref name="BBC1500" />，穆斯林禮拜的清真寺被暂时关闭<ref name="bbcJ102">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8143554.stm|title=Some Urumqi mosques defy shutdown|publisher=BBC News|date=2009-07-10|accessdate=2009-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712015957/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8143554.stm|archive-date=2009-07-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>。截至2010年1月仍存在对通信之限制<ref name="internetreopen2">{{cite news|work=China Tech News|date=2009-12-31|accessdate=2010-01-03|title=Internet Service In China's Xinjiang Will Soon Recover|url=http://www.chinatechnews.com/2009/12/31/11294-internet-service-in-chinas-xinjiang-will-soon-recover|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p3pQwkdp?url=http://www.chinatechnews.com/2009/12/31/11294-internet-service-in-chinas-xinjiang-will-soon-recover|archivedate=2010-04-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>及武装警察及民兵之街头巡逻<ref name="shadows" />。到2009年11月，超过400人因在混乱期间的暴力行为而面临刑事指控<ref name="riotwoman">{{cite news|author=Cui Jia|work=China Daily|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/cndy/2009-12/05/content_9122992.htm|date=2009-12-05|accessdate=2009-12-13|title=Riot woman sentenced to death for killing|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p3pUQAVM?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/cndy/2009-12/05/content_9122992.htm|archivedate=2010-04-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2009年11月，有9名嫌犯後來被定罪执行死刑<ref name="bbcnov">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/8350360.stm|title=Nine executed over Xinjiang riots|publisher=BBC|date=2009-11-09|accessdate=2010-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100930114704/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/8350360.stm|archive-date=2010-09-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==背景==

=== 历史背景 ===
{{further|维吾尔族|新疆历史|新疆的伊斯蘭化|东突厥斯坦独立运动}}
[[中华人民共和国|中华人民共和国]][[新疆维吾尔自治区|新疆维吾尔自治区]]位于[[中亚|中亚地区]]，区内约45%的居民为[[维吾尔族|维吾尔族]]，另外有约42%是[[汉族|汉族]]<ref name="2000census">《2000年人口普查中国民族人口资料》，民族出版社，2003年9月。ISBN 7-105-05425-5</ref>。该区之首府[[乌鲁木齐市|乌鲁木齐]]为清代[[乾隆|乾隆]]之后新建城市（舊名迪化），原本主要人口为满族和汉族<ref name="2000census" />。乌鲁木齐為高度工业化之城市，到2000年人口已达350多万，其人口大约75%是汉族，12.8%是维吾尔族，其他民族占人口的10%<ref name="2000census" />。

19世纪初，也就是清朝佔領新疆40年之后，北疆有大约15.5万汉族和回族人，是南疆维吾尔族人数的两倍多<ref>Millward, James A. (2007). ''Eurasian crossroads: A history of Xinjiang''. {{ISBN|978-0-231-13924-3}}. p. 306</ref>。19世纪早期的历史人口普查表明，汉族人口占30%，穆斯林人口占60%，但到了1953年的人口普查，汉族人口比例迅速轉變為僅為6%，维吾尔族人口占75%<ref name="ddx" />。但到2000年，汉族人口占40.57%，维吾尔族人口占45.21%<ref name="ddx">{{cite journal|title=Demographics and Development in Xinjiang after 1949|url=http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/EWCWwp001.pdf|last=Toops|first=Stanley|date=May 2004|publisher=East–West Center|issue=1|page=1|periodical=East-West Center Washington Working Papers|journal=|author=|access-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070716193518/http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/EWCWwp001.pdf|archive-date=2007-07-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。斯坦利·W·图普斯教授（{{lang|en|Professor Stanley W. Toops}}）指出，今天新疆的人口状况与清初相似。清政府在[[准噶尔灭族|准噶尔灭族]]后，在北疆引进了汉族、回族、维吾尔族、锡伯族和哈萨克族移民，北疆的回族和汉族占新疆总人口的三分之一，而南疆塔里木盆地的维吾尔族约占三分之二。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=GXj4a3gss8wC&pg=PA243#v=onepage&q&f=false ed. Starr 2004] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GXj4a3gss8wC&pg=PA243#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20190212214513 }}, p. 243.</ref>

维吾尔族和大多数中華人民共和國中央政府对于新疆地区之历史主张存在分歧：维吾尔族认为他们的祖先是当地的土著，而中華人民共和國政府认为现在的新疆自公元前200年左右就属于中国<ref name="Gladney">{{Cite book|chapter=The Chinese Program of Development and Control, 1978–2001|last=Gladney|first=Dru C.|year=2004<!--Book published in 2004, but this particular chapter was written in 2001-->|title=Xinjiang: China's Muslim borderland|url=https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star|editor=S. Frederick Starr|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-1318-9|pages=[https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star/page/n66 112]–114|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>。根据中華人民共和國政府之政策，维吾尔族被划分为少数民族<ref name="Gladney3">{{Cite book|chapter=The Chinese Program of Development and Control, 1978–2001|last=Gladney|first=Dru C.|year=2004<!--Book published in 2004, but this particular chapter was written in 2001-->|title=Xinjiang: China's Muslim borderland|url=https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star|editor=S. Frederick Starr|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-1318-9|pages=[https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star/page/n66 112]–114|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>。中华人民共和国主持了数百万汉人迁入新疆，他们在经济和政治上主導了这个地区<ref name="CACI3">{{cite web|title=Uyghur "separatism": China's policies in Xinjiang fuel dissent|url=http://www.cacianalyst.org/newsite/newsite/?q=node/364|accessdate=2010-01-29|date=2000-02-16|last=Rudelson|first=Justin Ben-Adam|publisher=Central Asia-Caucasus Institute Analyst|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229150459/http://www.cacianalyst.org/newsite/newsite/?q=node%2F364|archivedate=2012-02-29|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/opinions/new-frontier-same-old-problems/article1208363/|first=Wenran|last=Jiang|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2010-01-18|work=The Globe and Mail|title=New Frontier, same problems|page=parag. 10|quote=But just as in Tibet, the local population has viewed the increasing unequal distribution of wealth and income between China's coastal and inland regions, and between urban and rural areas, with an additional ethnic dimension. Most are not separatists, but they perceive that most of the economic opportunities in their homeland are taken by the Han Chinese, who are often better educated, better connected, and more resourceful. The Uyghurs also resent discrimination against their people by the Han, both in Xinjiang and elsewhere.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710011823/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/opinions/new-frontier-same-old-problems/article1208363/|archive-date=2009-07-10|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Timeboom">{{cite news|title=Why the Uighurs feel left out of China's boom|last=Ramzy|first=Austin|url=http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1910302,00.html?iid=sphere-inline-sidebar|work=Time|date=2009-07-14|accessdate=2009-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105163552/http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1910302,00.html?iid=sphere-inline-sidebar|archive-date=2012-11-05|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="winsandloses">{{cite web|title=How China Wins and Loses Xinjiang|url=http://www.foreignpolicy.com/articles/2009/07/09/how_china_wins_and_loses_xinjiang?page=0,0&obref=obinsite|accessdate=2009-09-05|author=|date=2009-07-09|last=Larson|first=Christina|format=|work=[[Foreign_Policy|Foreign Policy]]|publisher=|language=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608155032/http://www.foreignpolicy.com/articles/2009/07/09/how_china_wins_and_loses_xinjiang?page=0,0&obref=obinsite|archivedate=2011-06-08|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

中国之少数民族政策多基于所謂的[[肯定性行动|肯定性行动]]，加深了维吾尔族与汉族等其他民族的迥异的民族认同<ref name="bovingdon4">{{Cite book|last=Bovingdon|first=Gardner|title=Autonomy in Xinjiang: Han nationalist imperatives and Uyghur discontent|publisher=East-West Center|series=Political Studies 15|url=http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS011.pdf|location=Washington|year=2005|isbn=1-932728-20-1|page=4|postscript=<!--None-->|access-date=2014-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912055725/https://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS011.pdf|archive-date=2018-09-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="dillon51">{{Cite book|title=Xinjiang – China's Muslim Far Northwest|last=Dillon|first=Michael|year=2004|publisher=RoutledgeCurzon|isbn=0-415-32051-8|page=51|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>，但一些学者认为中華人民共和国政府非正式地倾向于基于多数的单一语言及单一文化之模式<ref name="Gladney2">{{Cite book|chapter=The Chinese Program of Development and Control, 1978–2001|last=Gladney|first=Dru C.|year=2004<!--Book published in 2004, but this particular chapter was written in 2001-->|title=Xinjiang: China's Muslim borderland|url=https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star|editor=S. Frederick Starr|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-1318-9|pages=[https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star/page/n66 112]–114|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref><ref name="Dwyer">{{Cite book|title=The Xinjiang Conflict: Uyghur Identity, Language Policy, and Political Discourse|last=Dwyer|first=Arienne|series=Political Studies 15|publisher=East-West Center|location=Washington|year=2005|isbn=1-932728-29-5|url=http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS015.pdf|page=2|postscript=<!--None-->|access-date=2014-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524134646/http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS015.pdf|archive-date=2010-05-24|dead-url=no}}</ref>。当局还严厉打击构成分裂主义的活动。这些政策，加上长期存在的文化差异，有时导致维吾尔族和其他民族尤其是非穆斯林民族之间的“怨恨”。一方面，由于汉族移民和政府政策，维吾尔族人的傳統伊斯蘭教法和行动自由受到限制<ref name=mooreblog>{{cite news | url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/malcolmmoore/100002509/urumqi-riots-signal-dark-days-ahead/ | title=Urumqi riots signal dark days ahead | work=The Daily Telegraph | date=2009-07-07 | accessdate=2009-07-07 | last=Moore | first=Malcolm | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004092133/http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/malcolmmoore/100002509/urumqi-riots-signal-dark-days-ahead/ | archive-date=2012-10-04 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=bovingdon34_35>{{Cite book | last=Bovingdon | first=Gardner | title=Autonomy in Xinjiang: Han nationalist imperatives and Uyghur discontent | publisher=East-West Center | series=Political Studies 15 | url=http://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS011.pdf | location=Washington | year=2005 | isbn=1-932728-20-1 | pages=34–5 | postscript=<!--None--> | access-date=2014-11-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912055725/https://www.eastwestcenter.org/fileadmin/stored/pdfs/PS011.pdf | archive-date=2018-09-12 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，而部分维吾尔族人认为政府低估了他们的历史和传统文化<ref name="Gladney4">{{Cite book|chapter=The Chinese Program of Development and Control, 1978–2001|last=Gladney|first=Dru C.|year=2004<!--Book published in 2004, but this particular chapter was written in 2001-->|title=Xinjiang: China's Muslim borderland|url=https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star|editor=S. Frederick Starr|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-1318-9|pages=[https://archive.org/details/xinjiangchinasmu00star/page/n66 112]–114|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>。另一方面，大多數汉族公民认为维吾尔族人受益于特殊待遇，例如高考加分制度、警察执法优待少数民族、优先进入大学、享受各種補貼、免于下崗和免于一胎政策<ref name="sautman29">{{Cite journal|title=Preferential policies for ethnic minorities in China: The case of Xinjiang|url=http://repository.ust.hk/dspace/bitstream/1783.1/1152/1/sosc32.pdf|last=Sautman|first=Barry|journal=Working Papers in the Social Sciences|publisher=Hong Kong University of Science and Technology|accessdate=2010-05-06|issue=32|year=1997|pages=29–31|postscript=<!--None-->|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721094447/http://repository.ust.hk/dspace/bitstream/1783.1/1152/1/sosc32.pdf|archive-date=2011-07-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并且“窝藏分裂主义的野心”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/608f0f80-6cac-11de-af56-00144feabdc0.html|work=Financial Times|title=Uighur riots show need for rethink by Beijing|first=Minxin|last=Pei|date=2009-07-09|accessdate=2010-01-18|quote=Han Chinese view the Uighurs as harbouring separatist aspirations and being disloyal and ungrateful, in spite of preferential policies for ethnic minority groups.|archive-date=2020-05-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200523192000/https://www.ft.com/content/608f0f80-6cac-11de-af56-00144feabdc0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

民族、宗教、文化的不同，东突厥斯坦独立运动以及国内外各方势力的催化，使得维汉两族之间存在着矛盾，导致近几年来出现多起示威及恐怖暴力活动<ref name="Hierman">{{cite journal | doi=10.2753/PPC1075-8216540304 | last=Hierman | first=Brent | title=The Pacification of Xinjiang: Uighur Protest and the Chinese State, 1988–2002 | journal=Problems of Post-Communism | year=2007 | volume=54 | issue=3 | pages=48–62}}</ref>。新疆长时间以来都爆发暴力恐怖主义事件，譬如1997年的[[伊宁二·五事件|伊宁二·五事件]]、2008年的[[2008年喀什袭击事件|喀什袭击事件]]与[[2008年夏季奥林匹克运动会|北京奥运会]]揭幕之前爆发的[[2008年新疆反政府示威|大规模动乱]]，以及无数小规模的恐怖袭击事件<ref name="CACI">{{cite web | publisher=Central Asia-Caucasus Institute Analyst | url=http://www.cacianalyst.org/newsite/newsite/?q=node/364 | date=2000-02-16 | accessdate=2010-01-29 | last=Rudelson | first=Justin Ben-Adam | title=Uyghur "separatism": China's policies in Xinjiang fuel dissent | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229150459/http://www.cacianalyst.org/newsite/newsite/?q=node%2F364 | archivedate=2012-02-29 }}</ref><ref name="Gunaratna">{{cite journal | last=Gunaratna | first=Rohan | page=59 | last2=Pereire | first2=Kenneth George | year=2006 | title=An al-Qaeda associate group operating in China? | volume=4 | issue=2 | journal=China and Eurasia Forum Quarterly | url=http://www.silkroadstudies.org/new/docs/CEF/Quarterly/May_2006/GunaratnaPereire.pdf | quote=Since [the Ghulja incident], numerous attacks including attacks on buses, clashes between ETIM militants and Chinese security forces, assassination attempts, attempts to attack Chinese key installations and government buildings have taken place, though many cases go unreported. | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110106144335/http://www.silkroadstudies.org/new/docs/CEF/Quarterly/May_2006/GunaratnaPereire.pdf | archivedate=2011-01-06 | access-date=2014-11-21 }}</ref>。

