[[File:Sauerbrey,_Kadeer_and_Seytoff_2006.jpg|right]]
此事件发生的几天前，[[广东省|广东省]][[韶关市|韶关市]]因维族工人性骚扰當地女子发生[[旭日玩具厂群体斗殴事件|一起斗殴事件]]<ref name=":0">{{cite news|author=申华|title=广东加紧处理韶关事件涉嫌人员|date=2009-07-07|publisher=VOA|url=http://www.voanews.com/chinese/w2009-07-07-voa52.cfm|work=|pages=|accessdate=2009-07-08|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710184654/http://www.voanews.com/chinese/w2009-07-07-voa52.cfm|archive-date=2009-07-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>。据官方媒体报道，6月下旬，一名心怀不满的前工人散布谣言，称两名汉族妇女被6名维吾尔男子强奸。官方消息人士后来说，他们没有找到任何证据来支持强奸指控<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.voanews.com/english/news/a-13-2009-07-07-voa6-68790522.html?CFTOKEN=39135411&CFID=286994581&jsessionid=de30e9333ac029fc1b14695a684c467c4e1c|title=Violence in Xinjiang Nothing New Says China Analyst|publisher=VOA news|first=Victor|last=Beattie|date=2009-07-08|accessdate=2010-01-18}}{{Dead link|date=2019年8月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=":0" />。6月25日至26日夜间，广东工厂的紧张局势导致维吾尔族和汉族之间爆发了全面的族群冲突，两名维吾尔族工人被打死<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8125693.stm|publisher=BBC News|title=Man held over China ethnic clash|date=2009-06-30|accessdate=2010-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707221534/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8125693.stm|archive-date=2009-07-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>。流亡的维吾尔族领导人声称死亡人数要高得多<ref name="bloomberg">{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aBWP2E9DJPlU|title=China Says 140 Die in Riot, Uighur Separatists Blamed (Update2)|date=2009-07-05|publisher=Bloomberg News|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924143852/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aBWP2E9DJPlU|archivedate=2015-09-24|accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref>。虽然官方新华社报道说，散布谣言的人已被逮捕，但维吾尔族人声称，当局没有保护维吾尔族工人，也没有逮捕任何参与鬥毆的汉族人。他们于7月5日在乌鲁木齐组织了一次街头抗议，表达他们的不满<ref name="nyt0907052" /><ref name="reut090705" />，并要求政府进行全面调查<ref name="GladneyInterview">{{cite podcast|title=Uighurs and China's Social Justice Problem|url=http://www.cfr.org/china/uighurs-chinas-social-justice-problem/p19760|host=Council on Foreign Relations|date=2009-07-09|accessdate=2010-01-17|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622095008/http://www.cfr.org/china/uighurs-chinas-social-justice-problem/p19760|archivedate=2011-06-22}}</ref>。
=== 最初的示威 ===
自7月5日晚开始，维吾尔人在烏魯木齊旅游景点大巴扎举行了抗议活动。据报道，人群聚集在人民广场一带<ref name="GladneyInterview" /><ref name="guardian" />。示威以和平方式开始，官方和目击者报告说，参加示威的有大约1000名维吾尔族人。世界维吾尔代表大会说，大约有10000名抗议者参加了示威<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nation.ittefaq.com/issues/2009/07/09/news0324.htm|title=China for unequivocal stand against ethnic separation|work=The New Nation|date=2009-07-09|accessdate=2010-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091016081238/http://nation.ittefaq.com/issues/2009/07/09/news0324.htm|archive-date=2009-10-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

7月6日，新疆维吾尔自治区主席[[努尔·白克力|努尔·白克力]]公布了前一天事件的官方时间表。根据时间表，当地时间下午5点左右，200多名示威者聚集在人民广场，其中约70名示威领导者被拘留。随后，人群聚集在解放南路、二道桥和山西巷的维吾尔族聚居区。到晚上7:30，一千多人聚集在山西胡同的一家医院门前。晚上7点40分左右，300多人封锁了人民路和南门地区的道路。 据白克力称，在警方“控制和驱散”人群后，暴乱分子于晚上8点18分开始捣毁公交车。<ref name="中新网">{{cite news|url=http://www.chinanews.com/gn/news/2009/07-06/1762907.shtml|script-title=zh:新疆披露打砸抢烧杀暴力犯罪事件当日发展始末|publisher=中新网 Chinanews.com.cn|date=2009-07-06|language=zh|access-date=2019-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703153802/http://www.chinanews.com/gn/news/2009/07-06/1762907.shtml|archive-date=2019-07-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>

示威活动是如何演变成暴力活动的尚不清楚<ref name="ai">{{cite journal|title="Justice, justice": The July 2009 Protests in Xinjiang, China|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/asa17/027/2010/en/|date=2010-07-02|publisher=Amnesty International|accessdate=2010-07-02|journal=|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150426050538/http://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/ASA17/027/2010/en/|archive-date=2015-04-26|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="afraidtoevenlook">{{cite journal|title=We Are Afraid to Even Look for Them: Enforced Disappearances in the Wake of Xinjiang's Protests|url=https://www.hrw.org/en/node/86103/section/6|date=2009-10-20|publisher=Human Rights Watch|accessdate=2010-01-18|journal=|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100103111733/http://www.hrw.org/en/node/86103/section/6|archive-date=2010-01-03|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="buqingchu">{{cite web|url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,,4511658,00.html|accessdate=2009-09-05|date=2009-07-23|publisher=Deutsche Welle|quote=<br />Interviewer: {{lang|zh-hans|您认为事件的过程已经非常清楚了吗？}} ''(Do you think the process of the riots has become clear?)''<br />Bovingdon: {{lang|zh-hans|不清楚，而且我觉得可以说很不清楚。}} ''(No, it's not clear, and I think you can say it's much unclear.)''|script-title=zh:美新疆问题专家鲍文德访谈|trans-title=Interview with American "Xinjiang problem" expert Gardiner Bovingdon|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090727095430/http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,,4511658,00.html|archive-date=2009-07-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有人说警察对抗议者使用了过度的武力<ref name="ai2">{{cite journal|title="Justice, justice": The July 2009 Protests in Xinjiang, China|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/asa17/027/2010/en/|date=2010-07-02|publisher=[[Amnesty_International|Amnesty International]]|accessdate=2010-07-02|journal=|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150426050538/http://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/ASA17/027/2010/en/|archive-date=2015-04-26|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="BBC090707">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8137432.stm|date=2009-07-07|accessdate=2010-01-18|title=Mass arrests over China violence|publisher=BBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930100858/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8137432.stm|archive-date=2009-09-30|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="lat090706">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jul/06/world/fg-china-protest6|title=140 slain as Chinese riot police, Muslims clash in north-western city|first=Barbara|last=Demick|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2010-01-18|work=Los Angeles Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812031604/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jul/06/world/fg-china-protest6|archive-date=2010-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>，世界维吾尔代表大会迅速发布新闻稿称警察使用了致命武力并杀死了“数十名”抗议者<ref name="WUCpressrelease1">{{cite web|title=WUC Condemns China's Brutal Crackdown of a Peaceful Protest in Urumchi City|url=http://www.uyghurcongress.org/en/?p=966|accessdate=2009-09-05|date=2009-07-06|publisher=World Uyghur Congress|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721161854/http://www.uyghurcongress.org/en/?p=966|archive-date=2011-07-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WUCpressrelease2">{{cite web|title=World Uyghur Congress' Statement on July 5th Urumqi Incident|url=http://www.uyghurcongress.org/en/?p=975|accessdate=2009-09-05|date=2009-07-07|publisher=World Uyghur Congress|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721161909/http://www.uyghurcongress.org/en/?p=975|archive-date=2011-07-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。热比娅声称在人群中有奸细。其他人则声称是抗议者挑起了暴力事件；例如，《纽约时报》援引一位维吾尔族目击者的话说，抗议者开始向警察投掷石块<ref name="nyt090705">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/06/world/asia/06china.html?ref=global-home|title=Riots in Western China Amid Ethnic Tension|work=The New York Times|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-07-05|last=Wong|first=Edward|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228024742/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/06/world/asia/06china.html?ref=global-home|archive-date=2013-12-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。政府的官方说法是，暴力事件不仅是抗议者发起的，也是由国外的维吾尔分裂分子有预谋和协调的。<ref name="chinad0907063">{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|title=Civilians, officer killed in Ürümqi unrest|agency=Xinhua|work=China Daily|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2010-01-18|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5OchhRX?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="cctv24">{{cite news|publisher=China Central Television|script-title=zh:视频-乌鲁木齐"７·５"打砸抢烧严重暴力犯罪事件新闻发布会|url=http://news.cctv.com/china/20090707/105812.shtml|date=2009-07-07|accessdate=2009-07-07|format=video|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5Op5Evk?url=http://news.cctv.com/china/20090707/105812.shtml|archivedate=2010-04-18|language=zh|dead-url=yes}}</ref>当地公安局表示，他们发现有证据表明，许多维吾尔族人从其他城市赶来参加暴乱，他们在暴乱前两三天就开始准备武器<ref name="xhweapons">{{cite news|agency=Xinhua|publisher=Chinaview.cn|title=Urumqi riots: Weapons prepared beforehand, division of tasks clear|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/21/content_11744210.htm|accessdate=2009-12-15|date=2009-07-21|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106161532/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/21/content_11744210.htm|archivedate=2012-11-06}}</ref>。

=== 局势升级及扩大 ===
警方以武力清场后，暴乱分子开始投掷石块，砸碎车辆，闯入商店，攻击汉人<ref name=nyt090705/><ref name=Timewestwar/>。开始至少有1000名维吾尔人参与暴乱，之后人数一度高达3000人<ref name=timesonline/>。《[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]》的简·马卡尼（{{lang|en|Jane Macartney}}）表示第一天的暴乱主要是“汉人被抢劫财物的维吾尔匪徒刺伤”<ref name=times-escalates/>。《[[澳洲人报|澳洲人报]]》认为宗教态度温和的维吾尔人也会被暴乱分子捅杀<ref name=shadows>{{cite news | title=The violence has ended in Urumqi but shadows remain in hearts and minds | url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/the-violence-has-ended-in-urumqi-but-shadows-remain-in-hearts-and-minds/story-e6frg6so-1225815346008 | last=Sainsbury | first=Michael | work=The Australian | date=2010-01-02 | accessdate=2010-01-02}}</ref>。尽管暴乱分子大多数是维吾尔人，但并非所有维吾尔人都很暴力，据傳言汉人和维吾尔人曾相互帮忙躲过袭击<ref name=kindness>{{cite news | work=Shanghai Daily | title=Kindness found amid the violence | | date=2009-07-09}}</ref>。约1000名警察被派驻到现场，利用警棍、实弹、[[电枪|电枪]]、催泪弹和水炮驱散暴乱分子，在全市范围内设置路障，布置装甲车<ref name="afp090706" /><ref name=guardian>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jul/05/china-uighur-riots-xianjing | title=Muslim Uighurs riot as ethnic tensions rise in China | last=Branigan | first=Tania | last2=Watts | first2=Jonathan | work=The Guardian | date=2009-07-05 | accessdate=2009-07-05 | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907001330/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jul/05/china-uighur-riots-xianjing | archive-date=2013-09-07 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=aljazeera>{{cite news|author=Agencies|title=Civilians die in China riots|url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2009/07/200975175832600179.html|publisher=Al Jazeera|date=2009-07-05|accessdate=2009-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090706011648/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2009/07/200975175832600179.html|archive-date=2009-07-06|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=ai/>。

[[File:Ürümqi_riots_video.ogv|250px]]
乌鲁木齐市长[[吉尔拉·衣沙木丁|吉尔拉·衣沙木丁]]在新闻发布会上表示，晚上8点15分许，部分示威者开始打架抢劫，推翻护栏，砸烂三辆公交车，之后被警方驱散<ref name=cctv2/>。8点30分，解放南路和龙泉街一带的暴力升级，示威者焚烧警察巡逻车，袭击路人<ref name=cctv2/>。不久后，人民广场到大西门及小西门一带有700到800人沿路“打架、砸东西、抢劫、烧东西、杀人”。9点30分，政府接到报告指3人死亡，26人受伤，伤者包括6名警察<ref name=cctv2/>。警方前往人民路、南门、团结路、延安路和新华南路的热点地区戒备。10点左右，警方控制市内主要路段和商业区，但暴乱分子继续在次要道路和小巷中流连，袭击汉人，推倒或焚烧车辆<ref name=cctv2/>。接下来两天，警方组建小队“清扫”全市<ref name=cctv2/>。全市实行严格的宵禁<ref name=HuG8>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8139065.stm | title=Troops flood into China Riot City | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-07-08 | accessdate=2009-07-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708012117/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8139065.stm | archive-date=2009-07-08 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，星期二晚上9点至星期三上午8点“全面交通管制”，“避免进一步骚乱”<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009xinjiangriot/2009-07/09/content_8407294.htm |title=Traffic curfew lifted, tension remains in Urumqi |agency=Xinhua |work=China Daily |date=2009-07-09 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713210706/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009xinjiangriot/2009-07/09/content_8407294.htm |archive-date=2009-07-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。官媒新华社报道指，警方认为闹事者计划在[[阿克苏|阿克苏]]或[[伊犁哈萨克自治州|伊犁哈萨克自治州]]等新疆其他地方组织骚动<ref name=BBC090707/>。南部的喀什爆发暴力示威<ref name=npr>{{cite news | url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=106318388 | title=China Ethnic Unrest kills 156 | publisher=National Public Radio | date=2009-07-06 | accessdate=2009-07-06 | work=All Things Considered | first=Anthony | last=Kuhn | first2=Melissa | last2=Block | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710022832/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=106318388 | archive-date=2009-07-10 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，《南华早报》指当地许多商铺关门停业，清真寺被[[中国人民解放军|中国人民解放军]]的一个排封锁。当地的维吾尔人谴责安全部队过分使用武力，“攻击示威者并抓捕50人”<ref name=SCMPeerie>{{cite news |title=An eerie silence after lockdown in Kashgar |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-08 |first=Will |last=Clem |page= A4}}</ref>。清真寺附近于7月7日再发生冲突，约50人遭逮捕。星期日的示威过后，[[喀什师范学院|喀什师范学院]]的12000名学生被关在校园内，该校明显有学生前往乌鲁木齐参加示威<ref name=SCMPcollege>{{cite news |title=Thousands of students detained at college |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-09 |first=Will |last=Clem |page= A3}}</ref>。

=== 伤亡及财产损失 ===
[[File:July_2009_Ürümqi_riots_-_VOA.ogv|thumb]]的报道]]
[[File:July_2009_Ürümqi_riots_-_July_7_-_VOA.ogv|thumb]]的报道]]
示威前几个小时，官方媒体指死者仅3人<ref name="reut090705"/><ref name="afp090706"/><ref>{{cite news | date=2009-07-05 | accessdate=2009-07-05 | url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2009/07/05/uk-china-xinjiang-unrest-idUKTRE5641D720090705 | title=Three killed in riot in China's Xinjiang region | last=Buckley | first=Chris | work=Reuters | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220124841/http://uk.reuters.com/article/2009/07/05/uk-china-xinjiang-unrest-idUKTRE5641D720090705 | archive-date=2014-12-20 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。首日晚上的骚乱过后，死亡人数剧增，到7月6日中午时分，新华社指已有129人死亡<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/06/content_11661240.htm |title=129 killed, 816 injured in China's Xinjiang violence |date=2009-06-06 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |publisher=Chinaview.cn |agency=Xinhua |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090709082604/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/06/content_11661240.htm |archivedate=2009-07-09 }}</ref>。之后几天政府消息来源（新华社及党政官员）中的死亡人数继续增加<ref name=reut140>{{cite news | url=http://www.asiaone.com/News/Latest%2BNews/Asia/Story/A1Story20090706-153071.html | agency=Reuters | publisher=AsiaOne News | title=China says 140 dead in Xinjiang unrest | date=2009-07-06 | accessdate=2009-09-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171029040007/http://www.asiaone.com/News/Latest%2BNews/Asia/Story/A1Story20090706-153071.html | archive-date=2017-10-29 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=XH156dead>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/07/content_11663866.htm |title=Death toll in Xinjiang riot rises to 156 |agency=Xinhua |date=2009-07-07 |access-date=2019-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227234412/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/07/content_11663866.htm |archive-date=2016-12-27 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=XH184dead/><ref name=xh192death>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/15/content_11713238.htm | title=Death toll of Urumqi riot rises to 192 | agency=Xinhua | date=2009-07-15 | access-date=2019-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100831002836/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/15/content_11713238.htm | archive-date=2010-08-31 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，7月18日官方最后一次公布消息时指197人死亡<ref name=CD197/><ref name=Xinhua197/>，1721人受伤<ref name=scmp20090717/><ref name=NYTtrials/>。世界维吾尔大会指死者约600人<ref name=bbc/>。

新华社没有立即公布死者的民族成分<ref name=npr/>，不过《泰晤士报》和《每日电讯报》的记者称受害者大多是汉人<ref name="mooreblog"/><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article6656359.ece | title=Chinese Han mob marches for revenge against Uighurs after rampage | work=The Times | date=2009-07-07 | accessdate=2009-07-07 | first=Jane | last=Macartney | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111011132121/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article6656359.ece | archive-date=2011-10-11 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。直到7月10日公布184名死者时，新华社才称其中有汉族137名、维吾尔族46名、回族1名<ref name=XH184dead>{{cite news | url=http://www.newsday.com/news/death-toll-from-china-s-ethnic-riots-hits-184-1.1306298 | title=Death toll from China's ethnic riots hits 184 | publisher=Newsday | agency=Associated Press | date=2009-07-10 | access-date=2019-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710091904/https://www.newsday.com/news/death-toll-from-china-s-ethnic-riots-hits-184-1.1306298 | archive-date=2019-07-10 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。死者包括暴乱分子<ref name=ai/>，官方指警方击毙12名袭击平民的暴乱分子<ref>{{cite news | last=Duncan | first=Max | date=2009-07-18 | accessdate=2009-07-18 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/19/idUSLI462648 | title=China says police shot dead 12 Uighurs this month | publisher=Reuters | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019095800/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/19/idUSLI462648 | archive-date=2013-10-19 | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.timesfreepress.com/news/2009/jul/18/china-says-police-killed-12-urumqi-rioting/?breakingnews | title=China says police killed 12 in Urumqi rioting | agency=Associated Press | date=2009-07-18 | accessdate=2009-09-05 | last=Wong | first=Gillian | publisher=Times Free Press | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011131821/http://www.timesfreepress.com/news/2009/jul/18/china-says-police-killed-12-urumqi-rioting/?breakingnews | archive-date=2012-10-11 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。暴动过后几个月，政府坚称伤者多是汉人<ref name=BBC1500/>，医院表示伤者三分之二是汉族<ref name=Timewestwar>{{cite news | work=Time | date=2009-07-20 | accessdate=2009-09-05 | title=China's War in the West | url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1909460-1,00.html | last=Elegant | first=Simon | last2=Ramzy | first2=Austin | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090717075647/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1909460-1,00.html | archive-date=2009-07-17 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，但世维会表示遇害者包括许多维吾尔人<ref name=BBC1500>{{cite news | date=2009-08-03 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8181563.stm | publisher=BBC News | title=Xinjiang arrests 'now over 1,500' | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090929212147/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8181563.stm | archive-date=2009-09-29 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2009年8月中国政府发布的官方报道指156名遇害的平民中有134名汉族、11名回族、10名维吾尔族和1名满族<ref name=XHaugustbreakdown>{{cite news | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | date=2009-08-05 | accessdate=2009-12-13 | title=Innocent civilians make up 156 in Urumqi riot death toll | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/05/content_11831350.htm | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090808151504/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/05/content_11831350.htm | archivedate=2009-08-08 }}</ref>。维吾尔族支持者依旧质疑官方数字，称维吾尔族的人数依旧低估<ref name=afraidtoevenlook />。此外，新华社还表示627辆车和633座建筑受损<ref name=xhinjured>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/12/content_11696865.htm |title=Number of injured in Urumqi riot increases to 1,680 |agency=Xinhua |publisher=Chinaview.cn |accessdate=2010-01-18 |date=2009-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090717044345/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/12/content_11696865.htm |archive-date=2009-07-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

乌鲁木齐市政府最初宣布会拿出20万元赔偿金，此外每位“无辜遇难者”会获得1万元的“丧葬费”<ref name=caijing/> 。后来，死者赔偿增加到42万<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/21/content_11741337.htm | title=Xinjiang doubles compensation for bereaved families in Urumqi riot | date=2009-07-21 | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | accessdate=2010-01-18 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826004420/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/21/content_11741337.htm | archivedate=2009-08-26 }}</ref>。市长吉尔拉·衣沙木丁表示赔偿工作至少花费1亿元<ref name=caijing>{{cite news | url=http://www.caijing.com.cn/2009-07-10/110196178.html | script-title=zh:"７·５"事件遇害者家属将获补偿21万元 | work=[[财经_(杂志)|财新网]] | date=2009-07-10 | accessdate=2010-01-18 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20120723201703/http://www.caijing.com.cn/2009-07-10/110196178.html | archive-date=2012-07-23 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 事件过后 ===
乌鲁木齐的气氛依然紧张，受邀进入市内的记者目睹中国军人与要求释放当局家人的维吾尔人间对峙。据维吾尔人说，他们的家人遭到“肆意”逮捕<ref name=times-escalates>{{cite news |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/china/article6655225.ece |title=Riot police battle protesters as China's Uighur crisis escalates |first=Jane |last=Macartney |work=The Times |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |location=London |archive-date=2021-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524093530/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。一名维吾尔妇女告知《每日电讯报》记者，警方于7月6日晚闯入维吾尔族聚居区，破门抓走正在睡觉的男人和男孩，至少有100人被带走。7月7日，官方表示已逮捕1434名暴动嫌疑犯<ref name="dt5769839">{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5769839/Eyewtiness-tensions-high-on-the-streets-of-Urumqi.html |title=Eyewitness: tensions high on the streets of Urumqi |first=Peter |last=Foster |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100704075645/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5769839/Eyewtiness-tensions-high-on-the-streets-of-Urumqi.html |archive-date=2010-07-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。7月7日，200到300名维吾尔妇女聚集游行，抗议当局“不分青红皂白”逮捕维吾尔男性<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/07/content_11664739.htm |title=Police arrests 1,434 suspects in connection with Xinjiang riot |agency=Xinhua |publisher=Chinaview.cn |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2009-07-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710013745/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/07/content_11664739.htm |archivedate=2009-07-10 }}</ref>。期间她们与警方产生了非暴力的对抗<ref name=womensprotest>{{cite news | work=The Daily Telegraph | date=2009-07-07 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5764906/China-riots-300-Uighurs-stage-fresh-protest-in-Urumqi.html | title=China riots: 300 Uighurs stage fresh protest in Urumqi | last=Foster | first=Peter | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710103537/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5764906/China-riots-300-Uighurs-stage-fresh-protest-in-Urumqi.html | archive-date=2009-07-10 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Fosterpolice>{{cite news | work=The Daily Telegraph | last=Foster | first=Peter | date=2009-07-09 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | title=Urumqi: criticism and credit for the Chinese police | url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/peterfoster/100002643/urumqi-criticism-and-credit-for-the-chinese-police/ | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026013753/http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/peterfoster/100002643/urumqi-criticism-and-credit-for-the-chinese-police/ | archive-date=2011-10-26 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。热比娅·卡德尔表示当晚“至少1万人”失踪<ref name=Reut20090729>{{cite news | last=Fujioka | first=Chisa | date=2009-07-29 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/29/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE56S1O020090729 | title=Uighur leader says 10,000 went missing in one night | publisher=Reuters | accessdate=2011-04-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130216090634/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/29/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE56S1O020090729 | archive-date=2013-02-16 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。[[人权观察|人权观察]]组织后来聲稱记录到43起维吾尔人在7月6日至7日的大规模搜捕行动中被警方带走后失踪的案子，而且这“仅是冰山一角”<ref name=BBC8317644/>。组织表示，截至2009年10月20日，这些二十出头的青年男子被非法逮捕后便不见踪影<ref name=afraidtoevenlook/>。

7月7日，汉人在乌鲁木齐组织大规模示威游行<ref name=bno>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8137824.stm| title=Riots engulf Chinese Uighur city| publisher=BBC News| date=2009-07-07| accessdate=2010-01-18| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930100239/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8137824.stm| archive-date=2009-09-30| dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=telegraphmob>{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5766327/Han-Chinese-mob-takes-to-the-streets-in-Urumqi-in-hunt-for-Uighur-Muslims.html | title=Han Chinese mob takes to the streets in Urumqi in hunt for Uighur Muslims | work=The Daily Telegraph | last=Foster | first=Peter | date=2009-07-07 | accessdate=2010-01-18 | location=London | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100516043055/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5766327/Han-Chinese-mob-takes-to-the-streets-in-Urumqi-in-hunt-for-Uighur-Muslims.html | archive-date=2010-05-16 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。多家西方媒体聲稱，示威汉人人数从“数百人”到10万人不等<ref name=telegraphmob/>。《泰晤士报》認為，汉族经常群聚在一起报复“维吾尔暴乱分子”，所以两个民族之间经常爆发小规模斗殴事件<ref name=times-escalates/><ref name=telegraphmob/>。警方施放催泪弹并设置路障驱散示威者<ref name=rte>{{cite news |url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2009/0707/china.html |title=Curfew in Chinese city of Urumqi |publisher=[[RTÉ|RTÉ]] |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090810055300/http://www.rte.ie/news/2009/0707/china.html |archive-date=2009-08-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，利用扩音器喊话，要求汉人“冷静”，“让警察办事”<ref name=telegraphmob/>。市委书记[[栗智|栗智]]站在警用车车顶上，用扩音器呼吁人群回家<ref name="dt5769839"/>。

7月8日，群众抗议得到平息，仅剩下零星暴力事件<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8147657.stm | title=Chinese police kill two Uighurs | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-07-13 | accessdate=2009-07-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090714011806/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8147657.stm | archive-date=2009-07-14 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/13/content_8423095.htm | title=Police shoot dead two suspects, injure another in Urumqi | work=China Daily | date=2009-07-13 | accessdate=2009-07-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090716231153/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/13/content_8423095.htm | archive-date=2009-07-16 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=SCMPconflict>{{cite news |title=Conflicting stories emerge after police shoot dead Uyghur pair |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-14 |first=Will |last=Clem |author2=Choi, Chi-yuk|page= A1}}</ref>。事发几天内，“数千人”打算离开城市，客车票价应声上涨五倍<ref name=bbcJ10/><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.france24.com/en/20090711-exodus-urumqi-authorities-death-toll-uighur-xinjiang-han-china | title=Exodus from Urumqi as authorities up death toll | work=France24 | date=2009-07-11 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712135415/http://www.france24.com/en/20090711-exodus-urumqi-authorities-death-toll-uighur-xinjiang-han-china | archivedate=2009-07-12 | accessdate=2019-07-10 }}</ref>。

7月10日，乌鲁木齐各大清真寺“基于安全考虑”关闭，当局表示举办星期五[[主麻日|主麻日]]大型集会可能会重新点燃紧张情绪<ref name=bbcJ10>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8143554.stm | title=Some Urumqi mosques defy shutdown | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-07-10 | accessdate=2009-07-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712015957/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8143554.stm | archive-date=2009-07-12 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=euronewsJume>{{cite news | url=http://www.euronews.net/2009/07/10/urumqi-mosques-closed-for-friday-prayers/ | title=Urumqi mosques closed for Friday prayers | date=2009-08-09 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | publisher=Euronews | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114092823/http://www.euronews.net/2009/07/10/urumqi-mosques-closed-for-friday-prayers/ | archive-date=2012-01-14 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。大批维吾尔人依旧聚集祈祷，警方于是决定开放两间清真寺，避免发生“事端”<ref name=bbcJ10/>。在白色清真寺祈祷完，数百名示威者抗议当局抓人<ref name=rtrj10/><ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8144146.stm | title=China reimposes curfew in Urumqi | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-07-10 | accessdate=2009-07-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090715021748/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8144146.stm | archive-date=2009-07-15 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，被防暴警察驱散，5到6人遭逮捕<ref name=rtrj10>{{cite news | last=Buckley | first=Chris | date=2009-07-10 | accessdate=2009-07-12 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/10/us-china-xinjiang-demonstration-sb-idUSTRE5691HI20090710 | title=Chinese police break up Uighur protest after prayers | publisher=Reuters | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130216071705/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/10/us-china-xinjiang-demonstration-sb-idUSTRE5691HI20090710 | archive-date=2013-02-16 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

8月初，300多人被逮捕。英国广播公司指出，总共有1500多人因暴动遭逮捕<ref name=BBC1500/>。《金融时报》估计的人数更高，指自稱内部人士者表示到7月中旬已有4000人被捕，乌鲁木齐的监狱人满为患，最近被捕的人去了解放军的仓库<ref name=FT5aa932ee>{{cite news | first=Kathrin | last=Hille | date=2009-07-19 | url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/5aa932ee-747c-11de-8ad5-00144feabdc0.html?nclick_check=1 | title=Xinjiang widens crackdown on Uighurs | work=The Financial Times | access-date=2019-07-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110001651/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/5aa932ee-747c-11de-8ad5-00144feabdc0.html?nclick_check=1 | archive-date=2014-01-10 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。维吾尔美国协会表示，事后多位维吾尔记者和博客主被捕，其中一位记者[[海莱提·尼亚孜|海莱提·尼亚孜]]因向境外媒体发声被判15年有期徒刑<ref>{{cite web |last1=Graham-Harrison |first1=Emma |title=China jails Uighur journalist for 15 years - employer |url=https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE66M1OX20100723 |website=Reuters |accessdate=2019-07-10 |date=2010-07-23 |archive-date=2020-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806131435/https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE66M1OX20100723 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而当中备受关注案子是[[中央民族大学|中央民族大学]]的维吾尔族经济学家[[伊力哈木·土赫提|伊力哈木·土赫提]]，事发两天后，他因批评新疆自治区政府被带走<ref name=rfajul082009>{{cite news | publisher=Radio Free Asia | url=http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/Tohti-07082009151608.html | title=Outspoken Economist Presumed Detained | accessdate=2009-07-12 | date=2009-07-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712064735/http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/Tohti-07082009151608.html | archive-date=2009-07-12 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=rfa0824en>{{cite web | publisher=Radio Free Asia | year=2009 | url=http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/tohtifreed-08242009163817.html?searchterm=None | title=Uyghur Economist Freed, Warned | accessdate=2009-08-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160628072801/http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/tohtifreed-08242009163817.html?searchterm=None | archive-date=2016-06-28 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=release>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/24/world/asia/24china.html?_r=1&emc=eta1 | work=The New York Times | title=Without Explanation, China Releases 3 Activists | last=Wines | first=Michael | date=2009-08-23 | accessdate=2009-08-25 | archive-date=2020-02-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207123727/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/24/world/asia/24china.html?_r=1&emc=eta1 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 各方反應 ==
===事件的指控===
新疆维吾尔自治区政府宣布此次事件为“典型的境外指挥、境内行动，有预谋、有组织的打砸抢烧严重暴力事件”<ref name="chinad090706">{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|title=Civilians, officer killed in Ürümqi unrest|agency=Xinhua|work=China Daily|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2010-01-18|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5OchhRX?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>，指责[[热比娅·卡德尔|热比娅·卡德尔]]和[[世界維吾爾代表大會|世界維吾爾代表大會]]为阴谋者，并称相当一部分维吾尔族暴乱分子是来自一千五百公里之外的[[喀什市|喀什]]、[[和田市|和田]]等[[新疆独立运动|东突厥斯坦独立运动]]比较盛行之地<ref name="cctv0711">{{cite web|publisher=中国中央电视台|title=参与打砸抢烧分子相当一部分来自喀什、和田等地|url=http://news.cctv.com/program/C21249/20090711/101814.shtml|author=|date=2009-07-11|accessdate=2009-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111118161308/http://news.cctv.com/program/C21249/20090711/101814.shtml|archive-date=2011-11-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。新疆维吾尔自治区主席[[努尔·白克力|努尔·白克力]]认为是境外[[三股势力|三股势力]]後来大肆炒作了旭日玩具厂事件，煽动上街游行示威，破坏民族团结和社会稳定<ref name="chinad0907062">{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|title=Civilians, officer killed in Ürümqi unrest|agency=Xinhua|work=China Daily|date=2009-07-06|accessdate=2010-01-18|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5OchhRX?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/06/content_8379985.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。政府消息来源引用[[热比娅·卡德尔|热比娅·卡德尔]]在西藏骚乱后的公开讲话和电话录音，称她在其中说在乌鲁木齐会发生一些事情<ref name="WUCbehind">{{cite news|work=China Daily|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/07/content_8389647.htm|title=World Uyghur Congress behind violence: expert|date=2009-07-07|accessdate=2010-01-18|agency=Xinhua|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5Og6Hvj?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/07/content_8389647.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[努尔·白克力|努尔·白克力]]还表示[[热比娅|热比娅]]在7月5日同国内通了电话，煽动了该次事件；而维吾尔在线、Biliwal等网站亦大肆煽动宣传、传播谣言<ref>{{cite web |title=新疆维吾尔自治区主席努尔·白克力谈乌市打砸抢烧严重暴力犯罪事件 |url=http://news.cctv.com/china/20090706/104689.shtml |website=央视网 |accessdate=2019-07-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926193336/http://news.cctv.com/china/20090706/104689.shtml |archivedate=2018-09-26 |date=2009-07-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。中国当局指控一名他们声称是[[世界維吾爾代表大會|世界维吾尔人代表大会]]主要成员的男子，称其通过传播一段暴力视频，煽动民族紧张关系，并在一个在线论坛上敦促维吾尔族人“以暴力反击汉人”<ref name="Mukadaisi">{{cite news|url=http://english.cri.cn/6909/2009/07/29/1221s504925.htm|title=Violence Video about Urumqi Riot is Fake|publisher=China Radio International|agency=Xinhua|date=2009-07-29|accessdate=2010-01-18|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5Olncg2?url=http://english.cri.cn/6909/2009/07/29/1221s504925.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。乌鲁木齐市市长[[吉尔拉·衣沙木丁|吉尔拉·衣沙木丁]]称抗议者通过[[腾讯QQ|QQ群]]等服务在网上进行组织活动<ref name=cctv2>{{cite news | publisher=China Central Television | title=视频-乌鲁木齐"７·５"打砸抢烧严重暴力犯罪事件新闻发布会 | url=http://news.cctv.com/china/20090707/105812.shtml | date=2009-07-07 | accessdate=2009-07-07 | format=video | archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5Op5Evk?url=http://news.cctv.com/china/20090707/105812.shtml | archivedate=2010-04-18 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。《[[中国日报|中国日报]]》断言，组织暴乱是为了煽动分裂主义，使中东恐怖组织受益<ref name="plantohelp">{{cite news|work=China Daily|date=2009-07-16|accessdate=2010-01-18|title=Urumqi riots part of plan to help Al-Qaeda|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/opinion/2009-07/16/content_8434355.htm|author=Wu Chaofan|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p5PCiEuQ?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/opinion/2009-07/16/content_8434355.htm|archivedate=2010-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nerve">{{cite news|work=China Daily|date=2009-07-18|accessdate=2010-01-18|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/18/content_8445811.htm|title=Xinjiang riot hits regional anti-terror nerve|agency=Xinhua|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090727125132/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/18/content_8445811.htm|archive-date=2009-07-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。热比娅否认煽动暴力<ref name="profile0503173">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4357607.stm|work=BBC News|title=Profile: Rebiya Kadeer|date=2005-03-17|accessdate=2010-01-04|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66fiuUvbF?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4357607.stm|archive-date=2012-04-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并辩称严厉的安保措施、对韶关事件的不满和“中国多年的镇压”，而不是分裂分子或恐怖分子的干预，引发了右翼抗议活动及其演变为暴力，维吾尔流亡团体声称，当警察过度使用武力驱散人群时，暴力就爆发了<ref name="Timewestwar" /><ref name="afp090706" />。《[[联合早报|联合早报]]》记者的调查将参与者分为三类：以大学生为主体的维吾尔族和平示威者、打砸抢行动的起哄者，以及恐怖暴力犯罪的主体——从南疆喀什、和田等地组织来的敢死队<ref>{{cite news|author=韩咏红|title=新疆暴乱在市民心中划出裂痕|date=2009-07-26|publisher=|url=http://www.zaobao.com/special/feature/pages/feature090727.shtml|work=联合早报|pages=|accessdate=2009-07-29|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090728055927/http://www.zaobao.com/special/feature/pages/feature090727.shtml|archive-date=2009-07-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。维吾尔族记者[[海莱提·尼亚孜|海来特]]则认为组织者不是世维会和热比娅，热比娅最多只是唆使者。骚乱发生时他在街上听到有人呼喊建立伊斯蘭政教合一政權的口号，于是推论真正的组织者是在新疆地区活跃的地下极端宗教组织“[[伊扎布特|伊扎布特]]”<ref>{{cite news|author=韩咏红|title=维族资深记者海来特： 暴徒呼喊“建政教合一国”，策划者或是“伊扎布特”|date=2009-07-26|publisher=|url=http://www.zaobao.com/special/feature/pages/feature090727a.shtml|work=联合早报|pages=|accessdate=2009-07-29|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090728150800/http://www.zaobao.com/special/feature/pages/feature090727a.shtml|archive-date=2009-07-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。各方都同意，抗议活动是事先组织的，但是对于其中的恐怖暴力是有计划的还是自发的意见不一<ref name="shadows_quote">{{cite news|title=The violence has ended in Urumqi but shadows remain in hearts and minds|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/the-violence-has-ended-in-urumqi-but-shadows-remain-in-hearts-and-minds/story-e6frg6so-1225815346008|last=Sainsbury|first=Michael|work=The Australian|date=2010-01-02|accessdate=2010-01-02|quote=There is little doubt [the WUC] helped promote protests, but there is no evidence they fomented violence.}}</ref>，对事件背后的紧张民族关系反映了分离主义倾向还是对社会正义的渴望亦无定论<ref name="GladneyInterview" />。
=== 国内反应 ===
事发当天和之后，移动手机服务和互联网服务受限。[[中国移动|中国移动]]切断手机服务“阻止事态进一步扩大”<ref name=ChinaMobilecut>{{cite news |date=2009-07-06 |accessdate=2009-09-05 |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/minority-riots-erupt-in-chinas-west-media-reports-140-deaths/485614/0 |agency=Associated Press |work=The Indian Express |title=Minority riots erupt in China's west, media reports 140 deaths |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710091546/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/minority-riots-erupt-in-chinas-west-media-reports-140-deaths/485614/0 |archivedate=2009-07-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当地的[[国际长途电话|国际长途电话]]也受阻<ref name=SCMPoverseas>{{cite news |title=Overseas media given freedom to cover unrest, but some areas still out of bounds |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-08 |first=Chi-yuk |last=Choi |author2=Wu, Vivian |page=A2}}</ref><ref name=DemocracyNowvideo />，互联网访问被锁定<ref name=reuters1>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/06/us-china-xinjiang-internet-sb-idUSTRE56513820090706 |title=China tightens Web screws after Xinjiang riot |first=Emma |last=Graham-Harrison and Yu Le |agency=Reuters |date=2009-07-06 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221084150/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/06/us-china-xinjiang-internet-sb-idUSTRE56513820090706 |archivedate=2011-02-21 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name=comm_cut>{{cite news |url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jgCunmDsXkld2DigXwP4Lel290og |title=Internet cut in Urumqi to contain violence: media |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110311081018/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jgCunmDsXkld2DigXwP4Lel290og |archivedate=2011-03-11 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，非本地网站受阻。[[半岛电视台|半岛电视台]]7月9日指，当地负责接待外国记者的海德酒店是全市唯一一处能上网的地方，但记者不能发短信或打国际电话<ref name=DemocracyNowvideo />。审查员删掉当地网站和Google上的许多小道消息<ref name=afraidtoevenlook />，然而[[Twitter|Twitter]]、[[YouTube|YouTube]]和[[Flickr|Flickr]]很快就出现了示威的照片和视频<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jlMPMzVRIgHQFdLL_ShBYw_af3Vw|title=Savvy Internet users defy China's censors on riot|last=Doran|first=D'Arcy|date=2009-07-05|agency=Agence France-Presse|access-date=2019-07-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121126055327/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jlMPMzVRIgHQFdLL_ShBYw_af3Vw|archivedate=2012-11-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同时许多新疆网站关闭<ref name=MissingLink />。事发将近一年后的2010年5月14日，互联网服务全面恢复<ref name=InternetRestored>{{cite news |title=新疆今日起全面恢复互联网业务 |date=2010-05-14 |accessdate=2010-05-14 |url=http://news.china.com.cn/txt/2010-05/14/content_20038848.htm |publisher=中新网 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100517023849/http://news.china.com.cn/txt/2010-05/14/content_20038848.htm |archivedate=2010-05-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[中国中央电视台|中央电视台]]播出汽车被砸民众被打的录像<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/world/killed-new-protest-put-down-china/story-e6frea8l-1225746704543?from=public_rss |title=156 killed, new protest put down – China |agency=Agence France-Presse |first=Dan |last=Martin |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |work=Adelaide Now |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120203155105/http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/world/killed-new-protest-put-down-china/story-e6frea8l-1225746704543?from=public_rss |archivedate=2012-02-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。官员重申党的路线。自治区主席努尔·白克力针对局勢和韶关旭日玩具厂事件发表长篇讲话，表示广东和新疆政府已妥善安置遇害工人，谴责暴力事件是“有组织、有阴谋的”<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.qq.com/a/20090706/000460.htm | title=视频:新疆自治区主席就打砸抢烧事件发表讲话 | date=2009-07-06 | accessdate=2010-01-18 | publisher=腾讯网 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090709221946/http://news.qq.com/a/20090706/000460.htm | archivedate=2009-07-09 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[新疆维吾尔自治区人民代表大会常务委员会|新疆人大常委会]]主任[[艾力更·依明巴海|艾力更·依明巴海]]谴责7月5日的暴动是“极端主义、分裂主义和恐怖主义”<ref name="netease1">{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/20/content_11734279.htm | title=Xinjiang to speed up legislation against separatism, regional top lawmaker | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | date=2009-07-20 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090722131006/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-07/20/content_11734279.htm | archivedate=2009-07-22 | accessdate=2019-07-10 }}</ref><ref name="abcnews1">{{cite news |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2009/07/20/after-riots-china-promote-antiseparatist-laws.html |title=After Riots, China to Promote Anti-Separatist Laws |work=The Jakarta Post |date=2009-07-20 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |agency=Associated Press |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090819051121/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2009/07/20/after-riots-china-promote-antiseparatist-laws.html |archivedate=2009-08-19 }}</ref>。

