荷兰和挪威出现暴力示威。中国驻荷兰大使馆遭到维吾尔社运人士袭击，窗户被砖头砸碎<ref name=rte/>，国旗也被烧毁<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/07/content_8388406.htm |title=FM: China strongly condemns attacks on its foreign missions |work=China Daily |accessdate=2010-01-18 |date=2009-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090918191744/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-07/07/content_8388406.htm |archive-date=2009-09-18 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当天使馆关闭<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/China-shuts-Hague-embassy-after-Xinjiang-protest/Article1-429595.aspx |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125064433/http://www.hindustantimes.com/China-shuts-Hague-embassy-after-Xinjiang-protest/Article1-429595.aspx |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-01-25 |title=China shuts Hague embassy after Xinjiang protest |work=Hindustan Times |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 }}</ref>，142人被捕<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aVSP2kYBZ4hs |title=Dutch Police Hold 39 Detained After Protests at China Embassy |agency=Bloomberg |accessdate=2010-01-18 |date=2009-07-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105055611/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aVSP2kYBZ4hs |archivedate=2012-11-05 }}</ref>。同时，约100名维吾尔人在挪威首都[[奥斯陆|奥斯陆]]中国大使馆门外抗议。11名被捕，但之后无罪释放<ref name=ap>{{cite news |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/31781735/ns/world_news-europe/ |title=Uighurs protest in Turkey, Norway |agency=Associated Press |last=Fraser |first=Suzan |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710074143/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/31781735/ns/world_news-europe |archive-date=2009-07-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[印尼伊斯蘭教|印尼伊斯蘭教]]联盟的示威者袭击[[雅加达|雅加达]]中国大使馆的门卫，呼吁向中国发动[[圣战|圣战]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/afp_asiapacific/view/442075/1/.html|title=Indonesians protest at Chinese embassy|date=2009-07-13|accessdate=2011-07-23|publisher=Channel News Asia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023064621/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/afp_asiapacific/view/442075/1/.html|archive-date=2012-10-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>。巴基斯坦表示部分伤害中巴关系的“因素”不会损害或动摇两国的利益<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nation.com.pk/pakistan-news-newspaper-daily-english-online/Politics/10-Jul-2009/Some-elements-out-to-harm-SinoPak-ties |title=Some 'elements' out to harm Sino-Pak ties |work=The Nation |date=2009-07-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713175919/http://www.nation.com.pk/pakistan-news-newspaper-daily-english-online/Politics/10-Jul-2009/Some-elements-out-to-harm-SinoPak-ties |archivedate=2009-07-13 |accessdate=2019-07-10 }}</ref>。斯里兰卡强调事件是中国内部事务，自信中国当局有能力恢复正常局面<ref>{{cite web |url=http://firstlanka.com/english/news/recent-riots-in-xinjiang-region-china/ |title=Recent riots in Xinjiang region, China |publisher=Sri Lankan News |date=2009-07-10 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110816103228/http://firstlanka.com/english/news/recent-riots-in-xinjiang-region-china/ |archivedate=2011-08-16 }}</ref>。

加拿大外交事务长{{le|劳伦斯·加农|Lawrence Cannon}}敦促用“对话和善意”解决不满情绪，防止局势进一步恶化<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/world/story/2009/07/06/china-protests.html |title=Chinese protests spread as deaths mount |publisher=CBC News |accessdate=2010-01-18 |date=2009-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100710104003/http://www.cbc.ca/world/story/2009/07/06/china-protests.html |archive-date=2010-07-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。奥巴马政府发言人表示美国对新疆的生命损失感到遗憾和深切的关切，呼吁各方保持克制<ref name=jg />。美国国务院发言人伊恩·凯利表示“中国当局恢复秩序，阻止暴力事件进一步发展很重要<ref>{{cite news |last=Buckley |first=Chris |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/08/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE5650SW20090708 |title=China's Hu Abandons G8 as Ethnic Unrest Continues |agency=Reuters |date=2009-07-08 |accessdate=2009-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130216070520/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/08/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE5650SW20090708 |archive-date=2013-02-16 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。”[[美国国际宗教自由委员会|美国国际宗教自由委员会]]对中国的镇压表示“严重关切”，呼吁独立调查事件并制裁中国<ref name=SCMPsanct>{{cite news |title=US commission urges sanctions |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-16 |agency=Agence France-Presse |page=A4}}</ref>。

[[藏人行政中央|西藏流亡政府]]建立者[[第十四世达赖喇嘛|第十四世达赖喇嘛]]发表声明称自己“对新疆日益恶化的局势深感悲痛和关切，尤其是生命的悲惨损失”“我恳请中国当局本着理解和远见的精神，在处理这一局势时保持克制”<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/world/835411/dalai-lama-concerned-over-china-riots |title=Dalai Lama 'concerned' over China riots |work=Ninemsn |date=2009-07-09 |publication-date= |accessdate=2009-07-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090711124819/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/world/835411/dalai-lama-concerned-over-china-riots |archivedate=2009-07-11}}</ref>。

[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]呼吁“公正独立”调查事件，要求释放“和平表达意见、履行言论、结社、集会权力”的人士，公平审判其他人<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/news-and-updates/news/china-must-investigate-156-deaths-during-protests-in-urumqi-20090707 |title=China must investigate 156 deaths during protests in Urumqi |publisher=Amnesty International |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100127103141/http://www.amnesty.org/en/news-and-updates/news/china-must-investigate-156-deaths-during-protests-in-urumqi-20090707 |archive-date=2010-01-27 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[人权观察|人权观察]]呼吁中国保持克制，允许独立调查事件，包括解决维吾尔族对地区政策的担忧。组织还表示中国在应对抗议时应遵守国际准则，只用恰如其分的武力<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hrw.org/en/news/2009/07/06/china-exercise-restraint-xinjiang |title=China: Exercise Restraint in Xinjiang – Government Should Allow Independent United Nations Probe |publisher=Human Rights Watch |date=2009-07-06 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117024821/http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2009/07/06/china-exercise-restraint-xinjiang |archive-date=2010-01-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。伦敦风险分析机构Stirling Assynt表示，阿尔及利亚的[[伊斯兰马格里布基地组织|伊斯兰马格里布基地组织]]计划袭击北非的中国工人<ref name=BBC-AQIM>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8149379.stm | title=China demands Turkish retraction | date=2009-07-14 | accessdate=2009-07-14 | publisher=BBC News | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090717095816/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8149379.stm | archive-date=2009-07-17 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/terrorism-security/2009/0715/p99s01-duts.html |title=China warns citizens in Algeria of Al Qaeda threat |last=Stack |first=Liam |work=The Christian Science Monitor |date=2009-07-15 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101122030727/http://www.csmonitor.com/World/terrorism-security/2009/0715/p99s01-duts.html |archive-date=2010-11-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5822791/Al-Qaeda-vows-revenge-on-China-over-Uighur-deaths.html |author=Moore, Malcolm |work=The Daily Telegraph |title=Al-Qaeda vows revenge on China over Uighur deaths |date=2009-07-14 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100417025917/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/5822791/Al-Qaeda-vows-revenge-on-China-over-Uighur-deaths.html |archive-date=2010-04-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 媒体报道 ===
[[英國廣播公司國際頻道|英國廣播公司國際頻道]]中國事務編輯陳世榮認為新華社的媒體處置手法有所改善：“為了更加可信，事發后幾個小時就有視頻出來了，而不用等兩個禮拜<ref name=bbc090706>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/8136944.stm |title=China clampdown on tech in Urumqi |first=Mark |last=Ward |publisher=BBC News |date=2009-07-06 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100629190434/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/8136944.stm |archive-date=2010-06-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”《每日電訊報》的{{le|彼得·福斯特 (新聞記者)|Peter Foster (journalist)|彼得·福斯特}}觀察到，資深的中國評論員都驚訝于北京抓住事件新聞議程的速度，他認為這是因為“中國沒有什麼好隱瞞的”<ref name=pfteleg090707 />。[[加州大學伯克利分校|加州大學伯克利分校]]的一位學者同意中國當局變得更加複雜<ref name=nyt090708>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/08/world/asia/08beijing.html |title=In Latest Upheaval, China Applies New Strategies to Control Flow of Information |work=The New York Times |first=Michael |last=Wines |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714112229/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/08/world/asia/08beijing.html |archive-date=2011-07-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》和[[法新社|法新社]]認為中國從全世界的政治示威，如所謂“[[顏色革命|顏色革命]]”的格魯吉亞[[玫瑰革命|玫瑰革命]]、烏克蘭[[橙色革命|橙色革命]]和伊朗[[伊朗綠色革命|綠色革命]]學到了一課，總結稱中國專家已經學習到現代電子通訊“幫助抗議者組織活動、接觸外面的世界，找到政府對付他們的辦法<ref name=nyt090708 /><ref name=AFP1 />。”

然而，{{le|詹姆斯鎮基金會|Jamestown Foundation}}的同僚威利·林（{{lang|en|Willy Lam}}）懷疑當局“只不過是在測試各方的反應”。他認為，如果此番開放收效甚微，那麼他們就會像[[2008年四川大地震|2008年四川大地震]]之後那樣“踩剎車”<ref name=AFP1 />。有外國記者被警方拘留，不久后獲釋<ref name=afraidtoevenlook />。7月10日，官員“出於他們的人身安全”，命令外國記者離開喀什<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.newssafety.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14481:foreign-reporters-ordered-out-of-kashgar&catid=422:china-media-safety&Itemid=100414 |title=Foreign reporters ordered out of Kashgar |publisher=International News Safety Institute |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=2009-07-10 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621063643/http://newssafety.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14481:foreign-reporters-ordered-out-of-kashgar&catid=422:china-media-safety&Itemid=100414 |archive-date=2010-06-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。新華社的最高官員夏林後來表示，雙方在騷亂前後爆發的暴力事件被官方的新聞頻道冷處理或完全不報，是因為擔心種族暴力擴散到烏魯木齊以外地區<ref name=nyt20100603>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/04/world/asia/04china.html?_r=2 |title=In Leaked Lecture, Details of China's News Cleanups |work=The New York Times |first=Andrew |last=Jacobs |date=2010-06-03 |accessdate=2010-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009112538/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/04/world/asia/04china.html?_r=2 |archive-date=2016-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[人民日報|人民日報]]》的一篇專欄文章斥責某些西方媒體報道“雙重標準，報道和評論有偏見”。文章指，中國不會因為開放和透明的態度接受部分境外政治人物或新聞媒體的“酬勞”。作者指出，“相當數量的媒體仍然有意無意地將暴徒的暴力行為的描述降到最低”，意圖將焦點放在所謂的種族衝突上<ref name=cnw20090710>{{cite news |url=http://world.people.com.cn/GB/9628529.html |title=国际观察：西方怎么不对恐怖袭击"保持克制"？！ |work=人民日報 |date=2009-07-10 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214061852/http://world.people.com.cn/GB/9628529.html |archive-date=2010-02-14 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。然而，[[法新社|法新社]]的達西·朵利（{{lang|en|D'Arcy Doran}}）歡迎對境外媒體的持續開放，但把他們的報道跟中國媒體的進行對比，指中方報道緊密追隨政府步伐，主要關注受傷的漢族，忽略了事件背後的“維吾爾故事”或原因<ref name=AFP1>{{cite news |url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5g4MmchS_uUQHaTfLOvi9Vm9XDHig |title=China extends hand to foreign media, but tightens grip elsewhere |first=D'Arcy |last=Doran |date=2009-07-09 |accessdate=2011-04-05 |publisher=Google |agency=Agence France Presse |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525164754/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5g4MmchS_uUQHaTfLOvi9Vm9XDHig |archive-date=2012-05-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

事件由[[路透社|路透社]]率先報道，該報道貼出了前一天騷亂的照片<ref name=SCMPphotogaffe>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/article/686136/posted-photos-source-western-media-gaffes |title=Posted photos source of western media gaffes |work=South China Morning Post |date=2009-07-08 |author=staff reporter |page=A4 |access-date=2019-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711073102/https://www.scmp.com/article/686136/posted-photos-source-western-media-gaffes |archive-date=2019-07-11 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這張顯示大批[[中国人民武装警察部队|武警]]隊列的照片，實際上是由《[[南方都市報|南方都市報]]》在6月26日的[[石首事件|石首事件]]中拍攝的<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nbweekly.com/magazine/cont.aspx?artiID=8848 |title=石首"抢尸"拉锯战 |publisher=南都周刊网 |date=2009-06-26 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714161604/http://www.nbweekly.com/magazine/cont.aspx?artiID=8848 |archivedate=2011-07-14 }}</ref>。其他新聞機構也誤用了這張照片<ref name=jaz090713>{{cite news |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/07/200971052926395491.html |title=Uighur group 'regrets' photo error |date=2009-07-10 |accessdate=2009-07-13 |publisher=Al Jazeera |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090714114122/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/07/200971052926395491.html |archive-date=2009-07-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，《每日電訊報》在網站掛了照片一天後才刪除<ref name=SCMPphotogaffe />。7月7日接受半島電視台採訪時，世維會領導熱比婭·卡德爾利用石首的照片為烏魯木齊的維吾爾辯護<ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/07/20097784613273384.html |title=Exiled Uighur leader denies stirring unrest |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |format=video |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091210062137/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/07/20097784613273384.html |archivedate=2009-12-10 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。一位世維會代表後來道歉，說這張照片是依照圖片質量從數百張中挑選出來的<ref name=jaz090713 />。

8月3日，新華社報道熱比婭的兩個孩子寫信責備她策劃騷亂<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/aug/03/xinjiang-kadeer-uighur-urumqi |title=China says Uighur leader's family condemn her |work=The Guardian |date=2009-08-03 |accessdate=2009-08-03 |location=London |first=Tania |last=Branigan |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907033006/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/aug/03/xinjiang-kadeer-uighur-urumqi |archive-date=2013-09-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。世維會德國發言人指信件系捏造。人權觀察研究院表示信件的新聞風格非常可疑，“接近”中國政府對騷亂及善後事件的說法。他補充道：“（她的孩子們）被掛在政府喉舌平台上廣泛傳播是非常不正常的<ref>{{cite news |agency=Agence France-Presse |date= 2009-08-03 |title =Uighur leader's family 'blame her' for unrest: report}}</ref>。”

2019年12月5日, [[中国环球电视网|中国环球电视网]]对外公布了一部名为《中国新疆 反恐前沿》的纪录片，其中包含关于此次事件的影像资料。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BjgSOYRZqIo |title=Fighting Terrorism in Xinjiang |date=2019-12-05 |accessdate=2019-12-07 |format=video |publisher=CGTV |language=en |archive-date=2019-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207184511/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BjgSOYRZqIo |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 后续和长期影响 ==
=== 逮捕和刑事檢控 ===
[[File:Vertical_Banner_Urumqi.jpg|thumb]]
8月初，烏魯木齊政府宣佈正式逮捕83名和騷亂有聯繫的人士<ref name=BBC83willbecharged>{{cite news | title=China 'to charge 83 over riots' | date=2009-08-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8184229.stm | work=BBC News | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090929212158/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8184229.stm | archive-date=2009-09-29 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=GTtrial>{{cite news | title=No trial date yet for Urumqi rioters | work=[[Global_Times|Global Times]] | date=2009-08-25 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://china.globaltimes.cn/chinanews/2009-08/460770.html | author=Qiu Yongzheng | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091216200440/http://china.globaltimes.cn/chinanews/2009-08/460770.html | archivedate=2009-12-16 }}</ref>。《[[中國日報|中國日報]]》8月底報道，被控罪的人數有200多人，審判將於8月底啟動<ref name=BBCtrials>{{cite news | title=Trials due over Xinjiang riots | date=2009-08-24 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8217427.stm | publisher=BBC News | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827155552/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8217427.stm | archive-date=2009-08-27 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=CNNtrials>{{cite news | title=Report: More than 200 face trial over China ethnic riots | date=2009-08-24 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/asiapcf/08/24/china.urumqi.riots/ | publisher=CNN News | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829220957/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/asiapcf/08/24/china.urumqi.riots/ | archive-date=2009-08-29 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。儘管自治區和地方的黨政官員否認該消息<ref name=NYTtrials/>，新疆當局後來宣佈向196名犯罪嫌疑人發出逮捕令，其中51人已被公訴。警方還請求檢察院再同意批捕239人，拘留825人<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-09/04/content_8653710.htm| title=Nearly 200 arrest warrants issued| work=China Daily| date=2009-09-04| accessdate=2009-09-04| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021081729/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-09/04/content_8653710.htm| archive-date=2012-10-21| dead-url=no}}</ref>。12月初，94名犯罪嫌疑人被逮捕<ref name=bbcfugitives>{{cite news | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-12-09 | accessdate=2009-12-13 | title=New arrests over China's Xinjiang ethnic riots | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8404245.stm | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091213133851/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8404245.stm | archive-date=2009-12-13 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

官方最初在9月底公佈了嫌疑人的刑事罪行，21人犯“謀殺、縱火、搶劫和故意毀壞財物罪”<ref name=21charged>{{cite news | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/26/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE58P0HR20090926 | title=China lays first charges over Xinjiang riots | date=2009-09-26 | accessdate=2009-09-28 | publisher=Reuters | last=Stanway | first=David | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130216110730/http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/26/us-china-xinjiang-idUSTRE58P0HR20090926 | archive-date=2013-02-16 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。10月11日，14000名特警前往烏魯木齊部署<ref name=XHsixdeath>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-10/12/content_12217174.htm | title=Six sentenced to death over Xinjiang riot | date=2009-10-10 | accessdate=2009-12-03 | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100115024341/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-10/12/content_12217174.htm | archivedate=2010-01-15 }}</ref>。翌日，新疆判處6人死刑，1人无期徒刑。六人都是維吾爾人，犯謀殺、縱火和盜竊罪。境外媒體表示判決似乎是在緩和大多數漢族的憤怒情緒<ref name=guardian20091012>{{cite news |title=China sentences six men to death over ethnic riots |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/oct/12/china-uighur-riot-sentencing |last=Watts |work=The Guardian |date=2009-10-12 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908051219/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/oct/12/china-uighur-riot-sentencing |archive-date=2013-09-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=China court sentences 6 to death in Xinjiang riots |first=Christopher |last=Bodeen |agency=Associated Press |work=USA Today |url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2009-10-12-china-riots-execution_N.htm |date=2009-10-12 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091018113612/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2009-10-12-china-riots-execution_N.htm |archive-date=2009-10-18 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，世維會譴責判決“政治化”，表示不會有公正審判的希冀<ref name=guardian20091012/>。人權觀察表示對21名被告的審判“嚴重違反正當程序”，“未達到正當程序和公平審判的最低國際標準”。具體來說，審判只花了一天時間，沒有事先公告，被告選擇的律師受到限制，並且黨指示法官如何處理案件<ref name=HRW20091015>{{cite web |url=https://www.hrw.org/en/news/2009/10/15/china-xinjiang-trials-deny-justice |title=China: Xinjiang Trials Deny Justice – Proceedings Failed Minimum Fair Trial Standards |date=2009-10-15 |accessdate=2010-01-18 |publisher=Human Rights Watch |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117033113/http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2009/10/15/china-xinjiang-trials-deny-justice |archive-date=2010-01-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不過另一方面，新華社指出訴訟程序以漢語和維吾爾語進行，並且判決前已仔細搜集核實證據<ref name=XHsixdeath/>。

2009年9月，九名死刑犯被處決，根據政府的聲明，8人是維吾爾族，1人是漢族<ref name=bbcnov /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5i86FMEClVmUn3KnSfvPjP7JuhHQA |title=China executes nine over Xinjiang unrest |publisher=Agence France Press |author=Barriaux, Marianne |date=2009-11-09 |accessdate=2010-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091226162427/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5i86FMEClVmUn3KnSfvPjP7JuhHQA |archive-date=2009-12-26 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。到2010年2月，被判死刑的人數增加到至少26人<ref name=26sentences>{{cite news | url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2010/01/26/uk-china-xinjiang-idUKTRE60P3HM20100126 | accessdate=2010-04-11 | date=2010-01-26 | agency=Reuters | title=China sentences four more to death for Urumqi riot | first=Yu | last=Le | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521124607/http://uk.reuters.com/article/2010/01/26/uk-china-xinjiang-idUKTRE60P3HM20100126 | archive-date=2011-05-21 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，包括一名漢族和一名維吾爾女性<ref name=riotwoman /><ref name=AP3sentence>{{cite news | last=MacDonald | first=Scott | agency=Associated Press | title=China sentences 3 more to death over ethnic riots | date=2009-12-04}}</ref>。

=== 后续骚乱和安保 ===
{{main|2009年新疆武警扣押香港記者事件}}
7月13日下午，[[天山區|天山區]][[白大寺|白大寺]]正在做[[晌礼|晌礼]]。一位男子突然站起试图抢夺白大寺[[伊玛目|伊玛目]][[阿布都西克尔·热合木都拉|阿布都西克尔·热合木都拉]]的话筒。在遭到制止后的几分钟以后，该男子再次站起并大喊：“我们要反抗！圣战！圣战！愿意跟我们的就一起走！”同时从怀中掏出一面表示“[[吉哈德|圣战]]”的绿色旗帜形标语。阿布都西克尔·热合木都拉当即结束礼拜，试图将该男子驱赶出清真寺。这时坐在第三排的另外两名男子从上面堆满袜子、下面藏有20多把刀的大包中抽出约60厘米长的砍刀，并大声喊道：“[[安拉|真主]]至大，跟我们一起进行圣战！”正好巡逻至此的[[天山区|天山区]]公安分局南关派出所一队民警击毙两名男子，击伤一名男子，伤者送往医院后不治身亡。<ref>{{cite web |title=白大寺坚拒暴徒煽动 |url=http://epaper.jinghua.cn/html/2009-08/03/content_448974.htm |website=[[京华网|京华网]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517234011/http://epaper.jinghua.cn/html/2009-08/03/content_448974.htm |archivedate=2014-05-17 |date=2009-08-03 |access-date=2021-06-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:Armed_Police_armored_vehicles_in_Urumqi_(3).jpg|thumb]]
8月中起，476人被{{le|皮下注射针头|Hypodermic needle}}刺傷<ref name=needlesquietsdown>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/04/content_11992622.htm | title=Urumqi quiets down after protest about syringe attacks | agency=Xinhua | date=2009-09-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905200708/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/04/content_11992622.htm | archivedate=2009-09-05 }}</ref><ref name=Bodeenneedles>{{cite news | publisher=Express India | agency=Associated Press | last=Bodeen | first=Christopher | title=Chinese city quiet after protests left 5 dead | url=http://www.expressindia.com/story.php?storyId=513227 | date=2009-09-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311141534/http://www.expressindia.com/story.php?storyId=513227 | archivedate=2012-03-11 }}</ref>。官方認為襲擊針對漢人，由維吾爾分裂分子策動<ref name=BBCneedles>{{cite news | publisher=BBC News | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8237259.stm | title=Chinese break up 'needle' riots | date=2009-09-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090904100934/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8237259.stm | archive-date=2009-09-04 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。漢族擔心這次襲擊<ref name=RFAnewriots>{{cite news | publisher=Radio Free Asia | date=2009-09-03 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | title=New Protests in Urumqi | url=http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/newprotests-09032009122558.html | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905191125/http://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/newprotests-09032009122558.html | archive-date=2009-09-05 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，不滿政府起訴騷亂分子的行動緩慢，在街頭發起數千人的抗議<ref name=APneedles>{{cite news | work=The Guardian | agency=Associated Press | last=Bodeen | first=Christopher | date=2009-09-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/feedarticle/8692201 | title=China official: 5 killed during Urumqi protests | location=London | archive-date=2021-05-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524093548/https://www.theguardian.com/info/2015/dec/09/removed-news-agency-feed-article | dead-url=no }}</ref>。9月3日的一場抗議活動導致5人死亡，14人受傷<ref name=tensionshighafter>{{cite news | publisher=Al Jazeera | title=Tensions high after Urumqi unrest | url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/09/2009954184928330.html | date=2009-09-05 | accessdate=2009-09-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905160817/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/asia-pacific/2009/09/2009954184928330.html | archive-date=2009-09-05 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=BBC5die>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8238768.stm | publisher=BBC News | date=2009-09-04 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | title='Five die' in China ethnic unrest | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090906004000/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8238768.stm | archive-date=2009-09-06 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。翌日，栗智被免除乌鲁木齐市委书记職務，市公安局局長刘耀华也被撤職<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/05/content_12001223.htm | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | date=2009-09-05 | accessdate=2009-09-05 | title=Urumqi party chief, Xinjiang police chief sacked | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090906225114/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/05/content_12001223.htm | archivedate=2009-09-06 }}</ref>。2010年4月，中共新疆黨委书记[[王乐泉|王樂泉]]被免職<ref name=Wang_replaced>{{cite news | publisher=BBC News | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8641443.stm | title=China replaces top Communist boss in Xinjiang region | date=2010-04-24 | accessdate=2010-04-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100426101628/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8641443.stm | archive-date=2010-04-26 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

針刺事件后城市恢復平靜，政府聲稱竭力保护人民群众生命和财产安全，從而導致武警依然出現在市面。2010年1月底，據報道警方每天會巡邏五到六次，夜間巡邏密度加強<ref name=shadows/>。事發一周年後，官方在烏魯木齊安裝4萬台[[电子监控探头|电子监控探头]]，“確保重點公共地方安全”<ref name=apfcamera>{{cite news | publisher = Agence France-Presse | title = 40,000 cameras keep watch on China's Urumqi | url = https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5ga3_wHMXBlX0nMPacpMjq8geGW8g | date = 2010-07-02 | accessdate = 2010-07-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120525164820/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5ga3_wHMXBlX0nMPacpMjq8geGW8g | archive-date = 2012-05-25 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 立法和调查 ===
8月底，中共中央政府通过一项法律，规定了“暴动、叛乱、大规模严重刑事暴力事件、恐怖袭击或其他社会安全事件”时出动武警的标准<ref name=NYTnewlaw>{{cite news |work=The New York Times |date=2009-08-27 |accessdate=2009-08-28 |title=China Approves New Law Governing Armed Police Force |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/28/world/asia/28china.html?ref=world |last=Wines |first=Michael |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009121859/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/28/world/asia/28china.html?ref=world |archive-date=2016-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=SecurityManagement>{{cite news |work=Security Management |date=2009-08-28 |accessdate=2009-09-04 |last=Harwood |first=Matthew |url=http://www.securitymanagement.com/news/china-legislature-outlines-police-powers-curbs-local-security-powers-006110 |title=China: Legislature Outlines Police Powers, Curbs Local Security Powers |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716034324/http://www.securitymanagement.com/news/china-legislature-outlines-police-powers-curbs-local-security-powers-006110 |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref>。9月初，政府发布公告，禁绝一切“未获许可的游行、示威及大规模示威”<ref name=banunlicensed>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/04/content_11996758.htm |date=2009-09-04 |accessdate=2009-09-04 |title=Urumqi imposes rules to ban unlicensed demonstrations |agency=Xinhua |publisher=Chinaview.cn |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090910021554/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/04/content_11996758.htm |archivedate=2009-09-10 }}</ref>。自治区政府也通过法律禁止使用互联网煽动民族分裂<ref name=MissingLink />。

11月，中国政府向新疆派遣400余名官员，包括[[中华人民共和国国务院秘书长|国务院秘书长]][[马凯_(官员)|马凯]]、宣传部部长[[刘云山|刘云山]]、[[中共中央统一战线工作部|统战部]]部长[[杜青林|杜青林]]等高级领导，组建新疆特设“调研队”，表面上研究应对暴力事件实行的政策调整<ref name="Liyuhui">{{cite journal|last=Li|first=Yuhui|year=2009|title=Notes on the Chinese Government's Handling of the Urumqi Riot in Xinjiang|journal=China and Eurasia Forum Quarterly|publisher=Central Asia-Caucasus Institute & Silk Road Studies Program|volume=7|issue=4|pages=11–15|issn=1653-4212|url=http://www.asia-studies.com/asia/SilkRoad/CEF/200912/cefq7.4yhl11-15.pdf|accessdate=2010-02-16}}{{Dead link|date=2019年8月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。2010年4月，新疆强硬派党委书记[[王乐泉|王乐泉]]被更爲溫和的[[张春贤|张春贤]]替代<ref name=nytaj>{{cite news|last=Jacobs|first=Andrew|title=Aid Fuels Change of Fortunes on Silk Road|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/11/15/world/asia/15kashgar.html?pagewanted=all|accessdate=2011-11-06|newspaper=New York Times|date=2010-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009114358/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/11/15/world/asia/15kashgar.html?pagewanted=all|archive-date=2016-10-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>。中央政府批准从东部省份向新疆转移支付150亿美元，支援自治区经济发展，宣布在喀什设立[[经济特区|经济特区]]<ref name=nytaj />。

中国在新疆部署了一张基层干部网络，主要集中在西北边境的穆斯林地区，应对社会风险，发现骚乱的早期迹象。数百名干部从新疆最贫穷的南疆地区转到了乌鲁木齐最不稳定的地区。有一条政策是，如果全家人都失业，政府就会为其中一位家庭成员安排工作。政府还宣布补贴大学生学费。贫民窟被重建为公寓楼，减少社会风险<ref>Hills, Kathrin (3 July 2010). "China deploys hundreds of social workers to ease plight of Uighurs", pg 1, ''Financial Times''</ref>。然而，独立观察员认为，需要解决的是不平等问题，思维定式需要改变才能取得成功。伊力哈木·土赫提警告称新政可能会吸引更多的汉族移民，进一步疏远维吾尔族人口<ref>Hills, Kathrin (3 July 2010). "Development unlikely to drown out disharmony", pg 4, ''Financial Times''</ref>。

=== 公共服务和互联网访问 ===
{{see also|中华人民共和国网络审查#新疆}}
公共交通于8月初完全恢复。新华社表示，267辆公交车在暴乱期间受损<ref name=Xinhuabuscomp>{{cite news | title=Public transportation companies receive 5 mln yuan Urumqi riot damage compensation | date=2009-08-26 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/26/content_11947636.htm | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829210417/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/26/content_11947636.htm | archivedate=2009-08-29 }}</ref>，到8月12日，大部分车次恢复使用<ref name=Xinhuabuses>{{cite news | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/12/content_11871249.htm | title=Public transport resumes full operation after Urumqi riot | date=2009-08-12 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | agency=Xinhua | publisher=Chinaview.cn | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090823021208/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-08/12/content_11871249.htm | archivedate=2009-08-23 }}</ref>。政府向公交公司提供总共525万赔偿<ref name=Xinhuabuscomp/>。交通服务的恢复，也使得政府鼓励游客到当地旅游，不过骚乱后旅游业收入锐减<ref name=shadows/>，10月国庆[[黄金周_(中国)|黄金周]]的到访旅客比去年较少25%<ref name=tourismslump>{{cite web | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-10/11/content_12210185.htm | title=Xinjiang receives fewer tourists after riot | publisher=Chinaview.cn | date=2009-10-11 | accessdate=2009-12-03 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106162535/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-10/11/content_12210185.htm | archivedate=2012-11-06 }}</ref>。

9月，乌鲁木齐的公办学校开始秋季学期，武警入驻戒备。许多学校的开学第一课是爱国<ref name=schoolopening>{{cite news | agency=Xinhua | date=2009-09-01 | accessdate=2009-09-04 | title=Hope the keynote as Chinese students begin new semester | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/01/content_11980940.htm | publisher=Chinaview.cn | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106162607/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-09/01/content_11980940.htm | archivedate=2012-11-06 }}</ref>。

另一方面，乌鲁木齐的互联网和国际电话服务在事发后受限将近一年。事件后[[新疆维吾尔自治区人民政府|新疆维吾尔自治区人民政府]]要求疆内各电信企业实施“三断一限”的局部通信管制，即切断出入疆互联网、手机短信息和国际长途电话，并对国内长途电话进行限呼<ref name=报道0122A/>。截至11月底，大多数网站仍遭到屏蔽，国际电话也不能拨打<ref name=MissingLink/>。12月底，主机设在自治区外的大多数网站仍然受限<ref name=TeaguevideoInternet>{{cite web | last=Teague | first=Matthew | format=video | url=http://worldblog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2009/11/25/4376537-could-the-uighur-unrest-spread | title=World Blog: Could the Uighur unrest spread? | publisher=NBC News online | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809143839/http://worldblog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2009/11/25/4376537-could-the-uighur-unrest-spread | archivedate=2011-08-09 | accessdate=2019-07-11 }} 1:41–2:15.</ref>，居民必须驱车到14小时车程的[[敦煌|敦煌]]才能正常上网<ref name=MissingLink>{{cite news | author=Cui Jia | title=The Missing Link | work=China Daily | date=2009-11-05}}</ref>。城内只能访问银行及地区政府网站等约100家当地网站。由于不能接听和拨打国际电话，因此乌鲁木齐的居民只能打电话给中国其他城市的中间人，经由他们拨打国际电话<ref name=MissingLink/>。通讯阻断甚至在中国引发争议：[[浙江大学|浙江大学]]的余潇枫批评该政策，许多乌鲁木齐当地的居民表示通讯不便阻碍业务往来，拖延恢复工作。然而，[[中欧社会论坛|中欧社会论坛]]的大卫·戈塞特（{{lang|en|David Gosset}}）认为，政府有权为了社会稳定关闭通信。当地人认为没有互联网改善了他们的生活质量<ref name=MissingLink/>。

12月底，政府开始逐步恢复服务。官媒新华社和《人民日报》的网站于12月28日恢复访问，[[新浪|新浪]]和[[搜狐|搜狐]]于2010年1月10日恢复访问<ref name=XHtexting>{{cite news | agency=Xinhua | date=2010-01-17 | title=Text messaging services resume in Xinjiang six months after riot | accessdate=2010-02-11 | publisher=English.news.cn | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/china/2010-01/18/c_13140684.htm | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106162617/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/china/2010-01/18/c_13140684.htm | archivedate=2012-11-06 }}</ref>，2月6日又有27家网站获得开放<ref name=CuiJiawebsites>{{cite news | url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-02/08/content_9440855.htm | title=More websites back online in Urumqi | author=Cui Jia | date=2010-02-08 | accessdate=2010-02-11 | work=China Daily | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100211171053/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-02/08/content_9440855.htm | archive-date=2010-02-11 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=CDmorwebsites>{{cite web | url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-02/10/content_9454925.htm | title=Across China: Xinjiang | date=2010-02-10 | accessdate=2010-02-11 | work=China Daily | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214005244/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-02/10/content_9454925.htm | archive-date=2010-02-14 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。然而只能看到网站部分内容，比方说，用户只能浏览论坛和博客，但不能发帖<ref name=trekking>{{cite news | publisher=BBC News | date=2010-02-11 | accessdate=2010-02-11 | title=Trekking 1,000 km in China for e-mail | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8506601.stm | last=Grammaticas | first=Damian | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100213224232/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8506601.stm | archive-date=2010-02-13 | dead-url=no }}</ref> 。《中国日报》表示遭限制的电子邮件服务于2月8日恢复，不过大约在同一时期写信的英国广播公司记者表示服务还不能用<ref name=trekking/>。手机短信服务于1月17日恢复，但用户每日发送的数量受限<ref name=XHtextrestored>{{cite news | agency=Xinhua | date=2010-01-18 | url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/china/2010-01/19/c_13141696.htm | title=Xinjiang to continue lifting communication restrictions: spokesperson | publisher=English.news.cn | accessdate=2010-02-11 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100506084341/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/china/2010-01/19/c_13141696.htm | archivedate=2010-05-06 }}</ref><ref name=BBCtextrestored>{{cite news | publisher=BBC News | accessdate=2010-02-11 | date=2010-01-18 | last=Bristow | first=Michael | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8464881.stm | title=China allows texting in Xinjiang six months after riots | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100121111539/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8464881.stm | archive-date=2010-01-21 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2010年5月14日7时40分许，[[中共新疆维吾尔自治区党委|中共新疆维吾尔自治区党委]]宣传部发表《致全疆广大网民朋友的公开信》，互联网全部恢复<ref name=InternetRestored/><ref name=报道0122A>{{cite news |author1=新华网 |title=新疆通信管制取消 关闭近一年的互联网全面开通 |url=http://www.scio.gov.cn/dfbd/dfbd/Document/636753/636753.htm |accessdate=2022-01-22 |agency=国务院新闻办公室 |archive-date=2022-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122032310/http://www.scio.gov.cn/dfbd/dfbd/Document/636753/636753.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

